Hi Folks,

    As many of you probably know, there's been a little bit of debate
on TCP-IP about what to name the NIC.  The issue is how to name the
NIC which makes it clear that it is a network service, independent
of provider.

    Now I thought we'd developed something approaching a consensus
that the proper naming space for such hosts was in .NET, and that
we'd already started properly naming hosts in this fashion, viz:

	    *.nyser.net
	    *.cs.net
	    *.nsf.net
	    *.uu.net

So, logically the nic would become something in *.defense-data.net
or *.inter.net or something (I don't really care precisely what the
second-level name is).

Am I mistaken?

Craig

